"script": "At this very moment, lightning is striking the Earth about 100 times every single second. That adds up to nearly 8 million bolts a day, crackling out of roughly 2,000 thunderstorms raging all at once. You see, each strike is hotter than the surface of the Sun, five times over. And a single bolt carries enough raw energy to power an average home for weeks. So in the time it took you to read this sentence, a few hundred lightning bolts have already torn through the sky somewhere on the planet, and you never felt a thing.",
